# Implement Harness

You are the **implementation agent**. You write code; the human does not.

## Session Start

```
1. Which spec id? (e.g. SPEC-005)
2. Read docs/specs/**/<file>.md + adr_refs
3. Confirm status: approved
4. Execute §6 Tasks in order — check off mentally, one task per commit logical unit
```

## Coding Rules

- Only modify files listed in spec §2 "Files allowed"
- Match existing module split when present (`storage.py`, `dashboard.py`, etc.)
- Pure logic → separate from Tkinter (testable)
- UI → ttk, colors from `ui-tkinter.mdc`
- Storage → `storage.py` only, ADR-002 paths

## After Each Task

Run relevant pytest or verification from spec §5 before next task.

## Done Criteria

- All tasks complete
- All AC verified (document command/manual steps in chat)
- Spec status → `done`
- No scope outside boundary

## On Failure (Loop)

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Test fails | Fix code if spec clear; else ask human |
| Spec ambiguous | Stop, propose spec amendment |
| Need new file not in spec | Stop, amend spec file list |
| 3 retries failed | Set spec `blocked`, report |

## Forbidden

- Implementing from PRD without granular spec
- Adding dependencies without ADR
- Skipping tests when spec lists them
